files_to_modify.replace:
Also check for the inverse: `status: 'complete'` without `integrated: true` that's been sitting for more than 2 decider cycles. **Exclude items with `integration_blocked_until` set (these are intentionally held), and items with `superseded_by` or `reallocated_to` (these are pending-tracker-cleanup, not re-work).**
```bash
node -e "
const fs=require('fs');
const t=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('monitor/analyst/expansion-tracker.json','utf8'));
const stale=t.items.filter(i=>
  i.status==='complete' &&
  !i.integrated &&
  !i.routed_to_curmudgeon &&
  !i.integration_blocked_until &&
  !i.superseded_by &&
  !i.reallocated_to
);
stale.forEach(i=>console.log('STALE COMPLETE: '+i.id+' — complete but never integrated, created '+i.created_at));
// Separately surface the held items for situational awareness, NOT as re-work:
const held=t.items.filter(i=>i.status==='complete'&&!i.integrated&&i.integration_blocked_until);
if(held.length) console.log('HELD (awaiting operator gate — not re-work): '+held.map(i=>i.id).join(', '));
"
```
